rComments:
Oh my gosh, this prof was a piece of work. She is so rude to students, so confusing in assignment expectations and shows extra "indulgence" in certain students. When a student brought to her attention that their group members weren't helping in the group assignment, her only comment was "try harder".

1/10 would never take again.

Don't bother asking questions, she'll see it as a personal offence and rip you to shreds. You're better off asking your classmates. Grading criteria was unclear like she herself didn't know what she wanted. The textbook for my class was so expensive and mandatory, she has no regard for people's living situations. I can't drop 160$ for fun.

Unclear grading criteria for marking participation disregards concerns and feedback of students. In syllabus says the class will go on for two hours but classes go for the full three hours. Would not recommend taking an online class with this professor!!

Yelled at a student for calling out her unfair and unspoken grading criteria. Very disrespectful to any students with any form of criticism. Will also require you to have a camera on (even if your living situations don't accommodate it).
Very engaging lectures. Her slides are very convoluted and hard to understand. Didn't bother going to lectures, like most people in the class.

The lectures were fun at the beginning but after everyone realized they were irrelevant to the exam half of the room was empty and I lost the motivation to interact with her Qs. Her tests are bad. All multiple choices and included mistakes sometimes. all in all was not a fun class to take and would not take her again.

didn't go to any lectures and still got an A from reading the slides and textbook. classes are not engaging at all but the tests are easy. It was annoying how she gave three tests, an essay, and a final exam for a first year course but an easy A nonetheless. Very nice and approachable, just not the most interesting.

The course is almost outdated in its material. She is a nice person but it is challenging to understand. The course is a media class yet she calls our phones mini computers doesnt know what Snapchat or instagram is haha!

She's brilliant and cares about the success of her students. The assessments were pretty fair, and she made the course a lot more interesting than it usually is. If you want to do well, just come to class, take notes, participate, and talk to her. I learnt a lot in class. Just take any class with her and expect the best.
